<figureCitation box="[553,621,1496,1522]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1982,2006]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,1625,1952]" captionTargetId="figure-380@6.[151,1436,1618,1959]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 9. Holotype of Robinsonia marahensis Laguerrre sp. nov., dorsal view on the left and ventral view on the right, labels are not to scale. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4982852" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4982852/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[645,836,1496,1522]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Head and thorax</emphasis>
. Antennae shortly bipectinate, shaft and rami brown, greyish beige at base, scape whitish. Frons dirty white, vertex pure white. Patagia, tegulae and thorax, white. Palpi dirty white underside, yellowish upper side, third segment very short.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4982852" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4982852" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4982852/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" startId="6.[151,250,1982,2006]" targetBox="[159,1427,1625,1952]" targetPageId="6">
